# AUTHORS — OO (Operating Organism) / llm-baremetal
#
# This file documents the intellectual property and contributions
# to this project. Git history is the authoritative record.

## Original Author & Architect

Djiby Diop (@Djiby-diop)
  - Project creator and sole architect (2024-present)
  - All original code, design, and architecture decisions

## Architecture & Systems designed by Djiby Diop:

  - OO (Operating Organism) concept and vision
  - Bare-metal UEFI boot system (efi_entry, efi_phases, 7-phase boot)
  - Custom memory manager (zones, arenas, allocator)
  - LLM inference engine without OS (Llama2 + GGUF + SSM)
  - OOSI binary format (v2 int8-quantized, v3 full standalone Mamba)
  - OOSI v3 loader and SSM recurrent inference engine
  - SSM/Mamba bare-metal integration (oosi_v3_loader.c, oosi_v3_infer.c)
  - HaltingHead mechanism (adaptive inference termination)
  - OO-SomaMind runtime contract
  - D+ policy engine (decision-making DSL)
  - Sentinel/Warden safety system
  - DjiBLAS (custom BLAS for bare-metal, AVX2 kernels)
  - Memory pressure as pain signal (oo-warden/pressure)
  - Hebbian arena learning (hot tensor reordering)
  - Split-brain dual inference (RATIONAL + CREATIVE paths)
  - Journal as auto-training dataset
  - OO-Bus inter-subsystem messaging
  - Hermes channel protocol
  - All OO modules: diopion, diagnostion, memorion, orchestrion,
    calibrion, compatibilion, synaption, conscience, immunion,
    symbion, metabion, pheromion, cellion, collectivion, dreamion,
    evolvion, ghost, morphion, neuralfs
  - REPL system with autorun, /ssm_load, /ssm_infer commands
  - USB boot image creation pipeline
  - GPT-NeoX tokenizer integration for Mamba models

## Third-party code incorporated (with attribution):

  - llama2.c by Andrej Karpathy (MIT) — base transformer inference
  - gnu-efi (BSD) — UEFI application framework
  - ARM optimized-routines (MIT) — expf() math functions

